# Crane ZDOTDIR shim — .zshenv.
#
# Crane points ZDOTDIR at this directory so it can load its shell integration
# WITHOUT editing the user's own startup files. The catch is that ZDOTDIR
# redirects EVERY per-user file zsh reads, not just .zshrc — so this directory
# ships a shim for all four (.zshenv, .zprofile, .zshrc, .zlogin), each one
# sourcing the user's real counterpart. Shipping only .zshrc silently dropped
# the user's ~/.zshenv, taking any PATH / EDITOR / env it exports with it.
#
# .zshenv is the first file zsh reads, so all the ZDOTDIR bookkeeping lives
# here:
#
#   CRANE_ZDOTDIR       this directory. ZDOTDIR has to point back here after
#                       every shim or the remaining shims never load.
#   CRANE_USER_ZDOTDIR  where the user's real startup files live: whatever
#                       ZDOTDIR held before Crane repointed it (handed over as
#                       CRANE_OLD_ZDOTDIR), else $HOME.
#
# The subtlety this file exists for: the documented way to relocate zsh config
# is to set ZDOTDIR from inside ~/.zshenv. Crane's GUI process never sees that
# value — zsh sets it at shell startup, it is not inherited by a GUI app — so
# CRANE_OLD_ZDOTDIR is unset for exactly the users who need it most. Sourcing
# the user's ~/.zshenv below and then re-reading ZDOTDIR recovers their real
# directory; restoring ZDOTDIR to Crane's afterwards keeps the later shims
# loading, so each one still knows where to find its user counterpart.
#
# Every source is guarded so a missing file is a no-op, and each is done at
# top level rather than inside a helper function: sourcing an rc from within a
# function would scope its `local` / `typeset` declarations to that function
# and quietly discard them.

CRANE_ZDOTDIR="${ZDOTDIR:-$HOME}"
CRANE_USER_ZDOTDIR="${CRANE_USER_ZDOTDIR:-${CRANE_OLD_ZDOTDIR:-$HOME}}"

if [[ -f "$CRANE_USER_ZDOTDIR/.zshenv" ]]; then
  ZDOTDIR="$CRANE_USER_ZDOTDIR"
  source "$CRANE_USER_ZDOTDIR/.zshenv"
  # The user's own .zshenv may have relocated ZDOTDIR — that new value is
  # where the rest of their startup files live.
  CRANE_USER_ZDOTDIR="${ZDOTDIR:-$HOME}"
fi

# Hand zsh back to Crane's directory so .zprofile / .zshrc / .zlogin resolve to
# the shims rather than straight to the user's originals.
ZDOTDIR="$CRANE_ZDOTDIR"
